The article discusses how the first president and first lady of the United States lit a diya together in the White House to celebrate Diwali, the Festival of Lights. They acknowledge the deeper meaning of this year's Diwali due to the pandemic and offer comfort to those who have lost loved ones. They express gratitude to those who celebrate Diwali in America and highlight the traditions and activities associated with the festival. The spirit of Diwali is described as bringing light, unity, and community. The act of lighting a diya is seen as a symbol of healing, repair, and renewal. The article ends with the family's well wishes for a happy Diwali.